Kano Governor Abdullahi Ganduje has explained why he anointed his Deputy, Dr Nasiru Gawuna, to succeed him in 2023. The Governor officially anointed Gawuna as the gubernatorial candidate of the All Progressives Congress (APC) during an APC stakeholders’ meeting at Africa House, Government House, Kano. Ganduje picked his former commissioner for Local Governments and Chieftaincy Affairs, Murtala Sule Garo as Gawuna’s running mate. -Advertisement- He said: “The decision to make my deputy the flag bearer was unanimously taken after exhaustive deliberations with all the stakeholders of the party. All party procedures were followed before arriving at this position.